{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Khrulkov et al. (2020) show that performing prototypical few-shot learning in hyperbolic space is competitive to Euclidean prototypical learning, even resulting in better accuracy scores when relying on a 4-layer ConvNet as the backbone.",
    "As a follow-up work, Gao et al. (2021) show that different tasks and even individual classes in few-shot learning favor different curvatures.",
    "They propose to generate a per-class curvature based on the second-order statistics of its in-class and out-of-class sample representations.",
    "Using the second-order statistics, a multi-layer perceptron with sigmoid activation is learned to fix the range of the curvature to [0, 1].",
    "Given classspecific curvatures, prototypes are obtained by constructing an intra-class distance matrix on top of which an MLP is trained."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Khrulkov et al. (2020) show that performing prototypical few-shot learning in hyperbolic space is competitive to Euclidean prototypical learning, even resulting in better accuracy scores when relying on a 4-layer ConvNet as the backbone.",
